page.title: 05Dwellings In Cobham
page.content: The village contains many terraced Georgian buildings and also a lot of houses built between 1910-1950. Surprisingly,though,there are not many Victorian buildings.The Darnley Arms is the only medieval building left-but the walls are concealed by a Georgian facade.There are a fair number of modern houses,but developement has been limited.In the main street the majority of the houses are terraced. The modern dwellings are detatched and semi-detatched houses and bungalows.There has been no 'estate' developement,and any proposals for new buildings has been carefully examined to ensure that the character of the village remains intact. The vast majority of the properties are owner-occupied.
